column4: <part_of.title>Christie's. Highly Important Paintings by Old Masters and A Drawing by Rembrandt, On Friday, June 26, 1964, London. [Notitie FG]: ''BRVEGEL' N° 6; FLEMALLE 44'; p. 4, N°6 Pieter Bruegel the Elder A Soldier  playing a fife, another a drum and a third raising a banner-signed and dated MDLXVIII-on panel-8in. by 7in. Collection: Possibly Choiseul-Praslin  [Notitie FG]: 'Speelman £24150; [losse bijlage]: Christie's Highly Important Paintings by Old Masters, On Friday, June 26, 1964: Addendum to lot 6: This picture bears a rare version of the stamp of the collection of King Charles I, CP in monogram, surmounted by a crown (Carolus Princeps). According to early inventories the picture was given to the King by Endymion Porter [...] We are indebted to Mr. Oliver Millar for this information.</part_of.title>
